info: Rating, 2 stars,  · February 2024,  · Stayed about a week
rating_comment:
The host was responsive to my texts. The area was nice, it was a rickshaw ride away from wherever I had to go within Uttara. I felt secured inside the house and in the neighborhood.
That marks the end of good things to say. The gatekeeper mr. joynal was a nightmare to deal with. His constants grunts and unwelcoming behavior made me think twice to come back here at night. I was in Dhaka for a marriage in the family and had to returned back only once around past 12AM. What a nightmare it was to face mr. joynal and hear his constant complains about opening the gate so late. My wife gave him 500 bdt before we left, which still bothers me because I don't think it was deserved.
The apartment itself was nice, a standard Uttara apartment so to say. But the mattresses were hard and stiff. Specially in one of the main bedrooms. We had to borrow mattress topper from friends before being able to use it. The kitchen was dirty, there were cockroaches running around there.

rating_comment: This is an excellent apartment to spend one’s vacation. The host responds to the guest’s needs promptly and resolves any issues right away. Awesome guest service. It feels like staying home. I recommend this place.

rating_comment: A nice and big house to stay. The location is pretty good as well. Loved it!

It was an amazing experience for me and my family to stay at this place. The host is an amazing person. He was very much helpful. The area was clean and the caretaker was so helpful as well. There is a cleaner on site for our help. The place is far better than the pictures. Hopefully in future if am staying anywhere in Dhaka then it will be this place every time.
Recommended this place 10000%
